modules.description: Provides functions to parse and render CommonMark-compatible markdown, including parsing text into an abstract syntax tree, converting the tree back to markdown, and handling inline elements. Operates on strings and a tree structure representing parsed documents. Used to transform user input into structured content for display or further processing.

Converts CommonMark strings to HTML, XML, man pages, LaTeX, and back to CommonMark, supporting customizable rendering options. Operates on an internal document type `t` derived from parsing input strings or files. Parses marked-up text for structured processing and renders it in various formats with controlled formatting parameters.
